# Test runs — targeted, not routine

Do **not** run `npm test` or belt/pathfinding tests as a default wrap-up after unrelated code changes.

## Skip by default

- No full `npm test` at the end of every task unless the user asks or the change clearly needs it.
- Do **not** run `tests/floorBeltCell.test.js` or corridor/belt integration suites unless the work touches pathfinding, HPA nav, floor belts, or belt puzzle templates.

## When to run tests

- User explicitly asks to run tests.
- Change is in or directly wired to: `Libraries/Pathfinding/`, `Systems/Navigation/`, belt nav behavior, corridor/HPA tests, or the specific feature's own test file.
- Prefer targeted runs (`node --test --test-timeout=5000 --import ./tests/testPreload.js tests/foo.test.js` or `node scripts/run-tests.mjs tests/foo.test.js`) over the full suite. Always use a **5s per-test timeout** — hangs fail instead of blocking forever.
- Do **not** use bare `node --test` (no timeout).
